https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/d0c7f870c29cdea5b13547f58b97983cfde9b345/src/nvim/eval/fs.c#L114-L115
The comment here probably left me with a bit of a bias – it makes me feel like wherever we only need string-level analysis, we should try to avoid calling real system path apis, so I naturally tend to keep them separate. And the name `os_fileinfo` also keeps making me feel like it implies call filesystem api, event though we could add a flag to control that.
Haha, anyway I'll try your suggest tomorrow. Just to confirm, you mean sth like this, right?
```c
typedef struct {
  uv_stat_t stat;  ///< @private
  size_t root_off;
  PathType type;
} FileInfo;
bool os_fileinfo(const char *path, FileInfo *file_info, bool no_stat) 
```
